SIMPLE: forehand
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forehand
<hw>Fore"hand`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>All
that part of a horse which is before the rider.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The chief or most important part.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Superiority; advantage; start; precedence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And, but for ceremony, such a wretch . . . ⟦br⟧
Had the <qex>forehand</qex> and vantage of a king.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forehand</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forehand
<hw>Fore"hand`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Done beforehand;
anticipative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And so extenuate the <qex>forehand</qex> sin.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forehanded</ent>⟦br⟧
